I had both lunch and breakfast at Couleur Cafe during a recent visit to Park Slope. Breakfast won, hands down. I ordered Bacon Concotte -- a pair of sunny-side-up baked eggs atop carmelized onions, proscuitto, and gruyere cheese. Yum! I chose greens for my side. So often breakfast out means a heavy meal, but this was both light and satisfying. To accompany it, I chose the turmeric latte -- delicious and beautiful. If I lived in this neighborhood, I'd be having this breakfast a lot.  My lunch, by contrast, was good but not especially interesting: a chicken sandwich with Swiss, tomato, avocado, and harissa mayo on baguette. It was the harissa mayo that swayed me to order it, but unfortunately, it didn't lend the sandwich the kick I was looking for. I almost didn't go back for breakfast, but I'm glad I did.
